    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Ok, it&#39;s you basic weed deck.  I use 8 pipeweed, and 7 pipes, and it really works wonders.  I don&#39;t need to stop at sanctuaries to heal, I can throw on burdens then remove them, I have twilight denial when I play stuff in Fellowship, and the weed let&#39;s me get through my deck a lot faster.  I don&#39;t use the Pony because most of my opponents will, and even then I like to draw Aragorn because if I just move early on and let my Nazgul empty my hand by the 3rd site I can usually get the weed rolling.<br />
<br />
The Nazgul is simple...2 of each, with some anti-archery in the form of All Blades Perish (works against dwarven might too) and Relentless Charge, so when they exhaust Legolas and Aragorn to kill someone, then I ABPerishimmer away and then kill them it&#39;s devastating.  The elven Allies and Bounder get lot&#39;s of play, and so does Tharin and the look on their faces when they bring him in to die and he gets Fear&#39;ed is priceless :).<br />
<br />
Let me know what you guys think, it&#39;s my first post! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000"> </Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">DeckTech <BR> For the Players, By the Players  <BR>www.decktech.net </FONT></TD></TR></table> 
